    "explanation": "<p>Given:</p>\n\n<p><p>Equilibrium constant, $ K_{\\text{eq}} = 20 $</p></p>\n<p><p>Temperature, $ T = 300 \\,\\text{K} $</p></p>\n<p><p>Gas constant, $ R = 8 \\times 10^{-3} \\,\\text{kJ}\\cdot\\text{mol}^{-1}\\cdot\\text{K}^{-1} $</p></p>\n\n<p>To find the standard Gibbs free energy change ($ \\Delta G^\\circ $), use the following equation:  </p>\n<p>$ \\Delta G^\\circ = -2.303 \\times R \\times T \\times \\log K_{\\text{eq}} $</p>\n<p>Substituting the given values:</p>\n<p>$ \\begin{aligned} \\Delta G^\\circ &= -2.303 \\times 8 \\times 10^{-3} \\times 300 \\times \\log 20 \\\\ & (\\text{given } \\log 20 = 1.301) \\\\ &= -2.303 \\times 8 \\times 10^{-3} \\times 300 \\times 1.301 \\\\ &= -7.191 \\,\\text{kJ}\\cdot\\text{mol}^{-1} \\end{aligned} $</p>",
